<1ST_LINE>r p AM-CVN-Reagan-Balloon     08-15 0093</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-CVN-Reagan-Balloon,100</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Reagan Cracks Joke as Balloon Pops</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan was in the midst of his
speech to the Republican National Convention Monday night when a
balloon popped.
   ``Missed me,'' he said quickly and went on without a pause.
That's become one of his favorite retorts to such sounds.
   A few moments later, in a series of statements that he began
with ``facts are stubborn things,'' Reagan misspoke.
   ``Facts are stupid things,'' he said and, just as quickly as
before, corrected himself to say ``facts are stubborn things.''
</TEXT>
