<HEAD>Dollar Lower, Stock Prices Rise Slightly</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Leads with 3 grafs to UPDATE with closing Nikkei, dollar.
Pickup 5th graf pvs ``Nearly the...''</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices rose slightly in Tokyo trading Monday,
while the dollar lost some ground.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues, the Tokyo Stock
Exchange's main barometer, closed at 27,901.29 points, up 67.78
points or 0.24 percent from last week's close.
   On the foreign exchange market, the dollar closed at 132.95 yen,
down 0.10 yen from Friday's close.
   ``Nearly the whole exchange is on vacation and hardly anyone is
selling their shares,'' said a securities dealer at a major
securities firm, speaking on condition of anonymity. ``The slight
gain in the Nikkei reflects the so-so situation in New York last
Friday.''
   Dealers also said investors are reluctant to participate in the
market ahead of the release of a U.S. trade report scheduled to be
announced Tuesday in Washington.
</TEXT>
