<HEAD>Coverage Plans for GOP Convention</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Here is a schedule of network coverage of the Republican
National Convention today, all times EDT:
   ABC, CBS and NBC will originate their evening newscasts from New
Orleans and plan live, prime-time coverage of the convention from 9
p.m. to 11 p.m.
   Hours of coverage are subject to change, the networks said.
   The major convention business in Monday night's session is
President Reagan's address.
   C-SPAN is carrying live, uninterrupted coverage of the session.
CNN also plans gavel-to-gavel coverage, with commentary and
interviews, as well as remote coverage from elsewhere in New
Orleans.
