<HEAD>Bush Ties To Ohio Noted</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   George Bush's ties to both New England and
Texas have often been noted, but now fans in the Buckeye state are
calling attention to an Ohio connection.
   Tahlman Krumm Jr., an assistant to Bush's Ohio campaign
chairman, said Sunday the vice president has ``a lot of roots in
Ohio.''
   Bush's father and grandfather both lived in Columbus, where his
father founded the Buckeye Steel Castings Co., and his wife,
Barbara, also has Buckeye connections.
   Her mother was a native of Marysville, and her grandfather was
once a justice on the Ohio Supreme Court, Krumm said.
   The vice president may not adopt Ohio, as he has Texas and some
New England states ``but he has a lot of kith and kin there,''
Krumm said.
   Krumm was tracing Bush's Ohio roots after Sunday's announcement
that Bush will be in Ohio next weekend.
