<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Obit-Pajetta     08-15 0129</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Pajetta,0132</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Italian Communist Party Official Dead at 73</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIVORNO, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Giuliano Pajetta, a member of the Italian
Communist Party's Central Committee and a former parliamentarian,
died today after a long illness, the party announced. He was 73.
   Pajetta began his political career in 1930, at age 15, when he
was arrested for anti-fascist activities. He fled Italy, first to
the Soviet Union and then to Spain, where he fought the fascists.
   In 1944, he became one of the organizers and leaders of the
Italian Resistance group ``volunteers for liberty.''
   After the war, Pajetta served in both the Chamber of Deputies
and the Senate of the Italian Parliament until 1972. He was a
member of the Central Committee of the Italian Communist Party
until his death.
</TEXT>
