<1ST_LINE>r i PM-France-Lafont     08-15 0170</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-France-Lafont,0176</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Army Called To Search For Missing Actress</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. ANDRE DE VALBORGNE, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 100 soldiers today
searched for a 26-year-old French actress who disappeared last week
from her mother's vacation home.
   Pauline Lafont, who has appeared in such films as ``The Summer
of Gentle Decline,'' was last seen Thursday when she told family
members she was going for a walk in the mountains near this village
about 45 miles northwest of Nimes.
   Police said they did not know what might have happened to Miss
Lafont.
   Her mother, Bernadette Lafont, also an actress, said she was
sure her daughter would not have run away.
   The soldiers were ordered to help police and rescue workers
search the rugged terrain of the Cevennes mountains, the army said
in a statement.
   Miss Lafont's brother, David, said she knew the area well and
took long hikes in the region. An earlier search was called off
Saturday, but David Lafont made a public appeal Sunday for help in
tracing his sister.
</TEXT>
