<HEAD>Man Charged With Murdering Estranged Wife By Ramming Car</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DECATUR, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man murdered his estranged wife and her
boyfriend by crashing his vehicle into their car, police said.
   Wesley R. Heckman, 44, ``was holding and cradling his dead
wife,'' when police arrived, Macon County sheriff's Lt. Roger
Walker said Sunday.
   Heckman was jailed on $500,000 bond on two counts each of murder
and reckless homicide.
   Linda Heckman, 44, and Michael R. Roberts, 35, died Friday when
their car was forced off a highway and overturned several times
south of Elwin, Walker said.
   Sheriff Lee Holsapple said Heckman confronted his estranged wife
when she got off work at St. Mary's Hospital, and chased her and
Roberts at speeds up to 90 mph.
   ``He had been ramming the car here in town,'' Walker said. ``He
chased them out of town and rammed them again.''
