<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Obit-Holmes     08-15 0129</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Holmes ,0132</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Canadian Foreign Affairs Expert Dies at 77</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TORONTO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   John Holmes, one of Canada's leading authorities
on foreign affairs, has died at the age of 77.
   Holmes, who died Friday in London, Ontario, was the former
director-general of the Canadian Institute of International
Affairs. He was also a Canadian diplomat from 1943 to 1960 with
postings in Britain, the Soviet Union and the United States.
   After a term as charge d'affaires at the Canadian Embassy in
Moscow, Holmes served for seven years as assistant undersecretary
in the Foreign Office until leaving government in 1960.
   He later joined the Institute of International Affairs and
became a professor of international relations at the University of
Toronto.
   Holmes wrote books and newspaper articles on Canadian foreign
policy.
</TEXT>
