<HEAD>English Si; Spanish No</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Several people attending a concert by Linda
Ronstadt walked out demanding refunds because she sang only in
Spanish and ignored cries from the audience to sing in English.
   The singer is on tour promoting her latest album that features
Mexican folk songs. Advertisements for the two-hour concert at
Great Woods in Mansfield Friday night promoted the concert as
``Linda Ronstadt: Canciones de Mi Padre'' or ``Songs of My Father.''
   ``What amazed us was that we weren't informed at all that the
whole show was going to be in Spanish,'' said Cheryl Manson of
Danvers. She said she got a refund for her $50 seat.
   ``Coinsidering that we were dressed for country, it was like we
had shown up at our own wedding dressed in jeans,'' she said.
   It wasn't known how many people actually left the concert, or
how many refunds were given, the Boston Herald said Sunday.
