<2ND_LINE>AM-Germany-Iran,0181</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Foreign Minister Discusses Hostage With Iranian Official</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Iranian envoy gave a letter
from his government to Foreign Minister Hans-Dietrich Genscher
during a meeting Monday in which an official said they discussed a
West German hostage held in Lebanon.
   A Foreign Ministry statement said Deputy Foreign Minister
Mohammed-Djabad Larijani delivered a letter from Prime Minister
Hussein Musavi intended for Helmut Kohl, the West German
chancellor. It did not say what was in the letter.
   The government official, who spoke on condition of anonymity,
said hostage Rudolf Cordes was among the topics of discussion in
the meeting Genscher and Larijani had at Frankfurt Airport.
Pro-Iranian Shiite Moslem extremists in Beirut kidnapped Cordes in
January 1987.
   According to the Foreign Ministry, Larijani and Genscher
discussed the cease-fire scheduled for Saturday in the Iran-Iraq
war, and ``bilateral matters.''
   ``Larijani discussed with the foreign minister Iran's position
as to the implementation of U.N. Security Council Resolution 598
and over the Geneva negotiations and over the reconstruction of his
(Larijani's) country,'' the ministry statement said.
