<HEAD>Scared By Moose, Stuck In Mud After Bad Shot</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FALUN, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The handicaps a young golfer encountered on
a course in this central Swedish town Monday were one enormous
moose and what may have been the muddiest swamp in Sweden, the
Swedish news agency TT reported.
   This is the account TT gave:
   After a badly hooked shot, the golfer went looking for the ball
among trees lining the fairway and found himself face-to-face with
a huge moose.
   Frightened, he ran deeper into the forest to escape the animal,
and promptly got stuck knee-high in a muddy swamp.
   Hours later, he was rescued by party of golfers who heard his
cries for help.
   The agency did not give the golfer's name.
   Nor did it say whether a moose and a quagmire were par for that
course.
