bite-sized pieces ``chicken tenders'' violated Burger King's
exclusive right to the name, a U.S. District Court jury concluded.
   The jury on Friday rejected Pilgrim's Pride's claim that
``chicken tenders'' is a generic term and should not be subject to
trademark regulations.
   Alan Greer, an attorney for Burger King Corp., said the
fast-food giant will file motions within 30 days seeking an order
from Judge Eugene Spellman to prohibit Pilgrim's Pride from using
the name.
