<1ST_LINE>r f BC-UnileverEarns     08-15 0191</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Unilever Earns,0199</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Households Products Group Posts 11 Percent Profit Gain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Unilever, the Anglo-Dutch household products
group, said Monday its second-quarter net profit jumped 11 percent,
with most lines of business contributing to the improvement.
   Unilever, whose brands include Lever, Lipton, and
Chesebrough-Pond's, said net profit in the three months ended June
30 rose to $371 million, or 20 cents a share, compared with $367
million, or 19.8 cents a share in the same period a year earlier.
   Sales gained 5 percent to $8.25 billion, from $7.84 billion in
the year-earlier period.
   ``The second quarter showed a stronger improvement over 1987
than that achieved in the first quarter,'' said Michael Angus,
chairman of the company's British arm, Unilever PLC. ``Most parts
of the business contributed to this result.''
   ``The outlook for the year as a whole is encouraging,'' the
chairman added.
   For the first six months of the year, net profit rose 8 percent
to $685 million, or 37 cents a share, from $696 million, or 38
cents a share in the first half of last year.
   Sales increased 4 percent to $15.9 billion, from $15.4 billion.
</TEXT>
